A giant silver clam shell and a giant chrome sperm whale rising from the reflecting pool are two popular interpretations of Thomas Klumpp 's design . Inside the Universum Science Center , opened in 2000 , are interactive exhibits also meant to provoke and engage the visitor : you can , for example , feel sound waves vibrate throughout your entire body .

Lucy the Elephant , Margate , New Jersey

Lucy was the first example of zoomorphic architecture in America , with the patent to prove it . Built in 1882 to sell New Jersey real estate , Lucy then found use as an office , a bar and a summer home . The patented 65-foot-tall tin and wood construction was meant to be one of a pack , but giant elephants did n't take off the way the architect intended . To this day , Lucy stands proudly alone .

